he Vedantic bent, is based on the final ta=\r\nrget rather than the path(s) one needs to walk, to get to the target. It as=\r\nsumes that you are already close to the target. It ends up misleading and c=\r\nreating wrong notions in unprepared sadhakas like &quot;all is delusion&quot;, &quot;every=\r\nthing is the same&quot;, &quot;what you do does not matter&quot;. The greatness of Bhagava=\r\nd Gita is that it talks about the path(s) as well as the target and has som=\r\nething relevant to everyone.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font=\r\n-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:t=\r\nransparent;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0,=\r\n 0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;backgrou=\r\nnd-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology=\r\n &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;\n href=\r\n=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/di=\r\nv&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial, helvet=\r\nica, clean, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;---=\r\n-----&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;border-left:2px solid rg=\r\nb(16, 16, 255);&quot;&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;f=\r\nont-size:10pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times=\r\n, serif;font-size:12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;font face=3D&quot;=\r\nArial&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &l=\r\nt;deleted&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&l